.TH "i3c_device_request_ibi" 9 "i3c_device_request_ibi" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
i3c_device_request_ibi \- Request an IBI
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" i3c_device_request_ibi
.BI "(struct i3c_device *dev "  ","
.BI "const struct i3c_ibi_setup *req "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device for which we should enable IBIs
.IP "req" 12
setup requested for this IBI
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is responsible for pre-allocating all resources needed to
process IBIs coming from \fIdev\fP. When this function returns, the IBI is not
enabled until \fBi3c_device_enable_ibi\fP is called.
.SH "RETURN"
0 in case of success, a negative error core otherwise.
